Comment.create(content: "George and Jim are in an explicit relationship for 17 years before Jim unexpectidly dies in a car crash. During the movie, set 8 months after Jim's death, George is clearly still in mourning but shows interest in other men. First Carlos, who he meets outside a liquor store and is emplied to be a sex worker (George gives him money but declines to actually pick him up). There is also Kenny, one of George's students, who shows clear interest in him. George is clearly conflicted about this. The two share some drinks and go skinny dipping but no further than that.", movie_id: 1 , user_id: 1)
Comment.create(content: "The movie is based on the novel by Christopher Isherwood. Isherwood was in a relationship with artist Don Bachardy for many decades and the novel seems to mirror some aspects of their relationship (Isherwood was older than Bachardy, similarly to the age gap between George and Jim).", movie_id: 1, user_id: 1)
